wikipedia_page.main: Fanny Jean Turing (1862 – 1 February 1934), Lady Trustram Eve, was a British politician.

response: *Fanny Jean Turing (1864–1934), politician and activist, was probably born in the village, where her father was vicar.

Born on 4 June 1865, Herbert Trustram Eve was educated at Bedford School. In 1893, he married Fanny Jean Turing, who later became a Conservative Party politician.Cheryl Law, Women: A Modern Political Dictionary, p. 61
*Fanny Jean Turing, Lady Trustram Eve (1864 – 1934), British politician
